  /tests

IMPLEMENTATION_RULES:
  - Treat every uploaded .3mf as a managed manufacturing artifact, not a random file blob.
  - Every project must have an owner, status, and at least one due-date or milestone.
  - A project can have multiple files and multiple print jobs.
  - A printer can have many historical jobs but only one active job at a time.
  - A material may be approved, restricted, experimental, deprecated, or retired.
  - Keep the catalog model flexible enough to support third-party brands and future materials without schema rewrites.
  - Design for human clarity first, then reporting accuracy, then automation.

SOURCE_AWARENESS_NOTES:
  Verified printer model references and selected vendor catalog references were checked against official vendor sources on 2026-04-23.
  This package ships with seed catalogs and an extensible ingestion architecture.
  It is not an exhaustive live mirror of every filament SKU sold globally.
  The system must therefore support:
    - seeded catalogs
    - manual CSV imports
    - admin catalog curation
    - future vendor adapter pipelines

SUCCESS_DEFINITION:
  A small to mid-size print engineering team can onboard, create printers, create materials, upload .3mf files, assign build work, and monitor active manufacturing operations in one place without using spreadsheets as the primary operational system.

END_TOON